3 SECTION 8. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 85.22C of Title 74, unless there
5 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. Each bidder and each recipient of a sole-source contract
7 shall accompany a bid with a written statement under oath disclosing
8 the following information:
9 1. Any known business or familial relationship then in effect
10 or which existed within one (1) year prior to the date of such
11 statement between any officer or director of the bidding company and
12 any officer or employee of the state agency receiving the bid;
13 2. The nature of any such known business or familial
14 relationships then in effect or which existed within one (1) year
15 prior to the date of such statement with any officer or employee of
16 the state agency receiving the bid; and
17 3. The names of all known persons having any such business or
18 familial relationships and the positions they hold within their
19 respective companies, firms, or state agencies.
20 B. If no business or familial relationships listed in
21 subsection A of this section exist, a bidder or recipient shall
22 submit a written statement under oath that no such relationships
23 exist.
